<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>Kanye CRUD for Bowie</title>
      <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
</head>
<body>


  <h1>Our future president, Kanye West, has a lot to say.</h1>

<h3>


<ul class="quotes">

  <!-- Loop through the quotes array and create strings ith the quotes[1].name + quotes[1].quote -->
  <% for(var i=0; i<quotes.length; i++) {%>
    <li class="quote">
      <span><%= quotes[i].quote %></span>
      <span><%= quotes[i].name %></span>
    </li>
  <% } %>
</ul>
</h3>

<h1>Let's keep track while we still can.</h1>
<p><h4>Use the form below to add your favorite Kanye-ism<br> and what internet forum he used to enlighten us with his genius.</h4></p>


<!-- FORM ELEMENTS EXPLAINED:
A form element can trigger a POST request. In this example, we need an action, a method, and a name for each element. Action tells the browser what path to go to. Method tells the browser what to send, so a POST. Name is what it is.
-->
<form action="/quotes" method="POST">
<input type="text" placeholder="Quote" name="quote">
<input type="text" placeholder="Forum" name="name">
<button type="Primary">I'm the Greatest</button>
</form>




</body>
</html>
